  "prompt": "How long does it take for teeth to relapse (move) after a broken retainer?",
  "response": "The time it takes for teeth to relapse after a broken retainer can vary significantly depending on several factors, including the duration since orthodontic treatment was completed, the individual's oral habits, and the severity of the original dental issues. \n\nFor some people, noticeable movement can begin within a few days to weeks, especially if the retention phase was recent and the teeth have not yet stabilized in their new positions. However, for others who have been wearing their retainers for years, the teeth may be more stable and exhibit minimal movement over the same period.\n\nIt's important to address any issues with a broken retainer as soon as possible by contacting an orthodontist. They can assess the situation and provide a replacement retainer or other appropriate measures to minimize any potential relapse.",
